summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of First Avenue South from the North line of the Eli B Maple Donation Claim to the north brick of the Duwamish River et al (in the City of Georgetown) now in the City of Seattle, by planking under Ordinance No. 491, creating Local Improvement District No. G-47 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
